</span></p><h3 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-hOGkXu NrNIR pf-74_ _Y6RW61"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-gyElHZ fxaypC pf-76_">Accident
</span></h3><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Accident_-_Dr_Richard_Dune.png?v=1687524586" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Accident_-_Dr_Richard_Dune.png?v=1687524586 1536w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Accident_-_Dr_Richard_Dune_500x.png?v=1687524586 320w" width="1707" height="960" alt="Accident - Dr Richard Dune -" title="Accident - Dr Richard Dune -" data-pf-type="Image3" class="sc-bXTejn eKvewz pf-77_"/><p class="sc-FNXRL jGHEAN pf-78_" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-gyElHZ fxaypC pf-80_">An accident is a separate, identifiable, unintended incident leading to physical injury or ill health. This includes acts of non-consensual violence against people at work. Understanding what constitutes an accident helps prevent and ensure a prompt response when they occur.
</span></p><h3 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-hOGkXu NrNIR pf-81_ _Y6RW61"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-gyElHZ fxaypC pf-83_">Hazard
</span></h3><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Hazard_-_Dr_Richard_Dune.png?v=1687524696" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Hazard_-_Dr_Richard_Dune.png?v=1687524696 1536w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Hazard_-_Dr_Richard_Dune_500x.png?v=1687524696 320w" width="1613" height="1075" alt="Hazard - Dr Richard Dune -" title="Hazard - Dr Richard Dune -" data-pf-type="Image3" class="sc-bXTejn eKvewz pf-84_"/><p class="sc-FNXRL jGHEAN pf-85_" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-gyElHZ fxaypC pf-87_">A hazard is anything with the potential to cause harm. This could be a substance, a process, a situation, or an environment. In care settings, these could range from physical hazards like wet floors to health hazards such as improper medication disposal.
</span></p><h3 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-hOGkXu NrNIR pf-88_ _Y6RW61"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-gyElHZ fxaypC pf-90_">Dangerous occurrence
</span></h3><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Dangerous_occurrence_-_Dr_Richard_Dune_4abea240-067b-43d1-ac5f-d42ecdfc0bc5.png?v=1687525111" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Dangerous_occurrence_-_Dr_Richard_Dune_4abea240-067b-43d1-ac5f-d42ecdfc0bc5.png?v=1687525111 1536w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Dangerous_occurrence_-_Dr_Richard_Dune_4abea240-067b-43d1-ac5f-d42ecdfc0bc5_500x.png?v=1687525111 320w" width="1808" height="1205" alt="Dangerous occurrence - Dr Richard Dune -" title="Dangerous occurrence - Dr Richard Dune -" data-pf-type="Image3" class="sc-bXTejn eKvewz pf-91_"/><p class="sc-FNXRL jGHEAN pf-92_" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-gyElHZ fxaypC pf-94_">These specific, unintentional events may not result in a reportable injury but potentially cause significant harm. Recognising such occurrences is crucial for preventing more severe incidents in the future.
</span></p><h2 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-hOGkXu NrNIR pf-95_ _Y6RW61"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-gyElHZ fxaypC pf-97_">Risk</span></h2><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Risk_-_Dr_Richard_Dune.png?v=1687525320" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Risk_-_Dr_Richard_Dune.png?v=1687525320 1536w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Risk_-_Dr_Richard_Dune_500x.png?v=1687525320 320w" width="1148" height="728" alt="Risk - Dr Richard Dune -" title="Risk - Dr Richard Dune -" data-pf-type="Image3" class="sc-bXTejn eKvewz pf-98_"/><p class="sc-FNXRL jGHEAN pf-99_" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-gyElHZ fxaypC pf-101_">Risk refers to the likelihood and consequences of harm occurring, such as someone slipping and falling on a wet floor. It is the cornerstone of many health and safety strategies, which aim to mitigate risk where possible.
</span></p><h2 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-hOGkXu NrNIR pf-102_ _Y6RW61"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-gyElHZ fxaypC pf-104_">Near miss
</span></h2><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Near_miss_-_Dr_Richard_Dune.png?v=1687525499" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Near_miss_-_Dr_Richard_Dune.png?v=1687525499 1536w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Near_miss_-_Dr_Richard_Dune_500x.png?v=1687525499 320w" width="1800" height="1200" alt="Near miss - Dr Richard Dune -" title="Near miss - Dr Richard Dune -" data-pf-type="Image3" class="sc-bXTejn eKvewz pf-105_"/><p class="sc-FNXRL jGHEAN pf-106_" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-gyElHZ fxaypC pf-108_">A near miss is an event that does not cause harm but holds the potential for injury or ill health. It's essential to report and investigate these instances as they are important indicators of where harm could occur.
</span></p><h2 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-hOGkXu NrNIR pf-109_ _Y6RW61"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-gyElHZ fxaypC pf-111_">Risk assessment

</span></h2><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Risk_assessment_-_Dr_Richard_Dune.png?v=1687527151" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Risk_assessment_-_Dr_Richard_Dune.png?v=1687527151 1536w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Risk_assessment_-_Dr_Richard_Dune_500x.png?v=1687527151 320w" width="1440" height="960" alt="Risk assessment - Dr Richard Dune -" title="Risk assessment - Dr Richard Dune -" data-pf-type="Image3" class="sc-bXTejn eKvewz pf-112_"/><p class="sc-FNXRL jGHEAN pf-113_" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-gyElHZ fxaypC pf-115_">Risk assessments are processes of identifying existing or potential hazards in the workplace. A well-conducted risk assessment helps to prevent accidents and ill health, ensuring a safer environment for employees and visitors.
</span></p><h2 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-hOGkXu NrNIR pf-116_ _Y6RW61"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-gyElHZ fxaypC pf-118_">Significant risk
</span></h2><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Significant_risk_-_Dr_Richard_Dune.png?v=1687527260" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Significant_risk_-_Dr_Richard_Dune.png?v=1687527260 1536w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Significant_risk_-_Dr_Richard_Dune_500x.png?v=1687527260 320w" width="1721" height="1145" alt="Significant risk - Dr Richard Dune -" title="Significant risk - Dr Richard Dune -" data-pf-type="Image3" class="sc-bXTejn eKvewz pf-119_"/><p class="sc-FNXRL jGHEAN pf-120_" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-gyElHZ fxaypC pf-122_">Significant risks are those with a high probability of occurring, posing a substantial risk to health and safety. Immediate action is required to control these risks, considering the cost includes time, effort, and finances.
</span></p><h3 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-hOGkXu NrNIR pf-123_ _Y6RW61"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-gyElHZ fxaypC pf-125_">Safe
</span></h3><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Safe_-_Dr_Richard_Dune.png?v=1687527344" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Safe_-_Dr_Richard_Dune.png?v=1687527344 1536w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Safe_-_Dr_Richard_Dune_500x.png?v=1687527344 320w" width="1244" height="829" alt="Safe - Dr Richard Dune -" title="Safe - Dr Richard Dune -" data-pf-type="Image3" class="sc-bXTejn eKvewz pf-126_"/><p class="sc-FNXRL jGHEAN pf-127_" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-gyElHZ fxaypC pf-129_">Being safe is about being protected from or not exposed to danger or risk. Creating a 'safe' environment is the ultimate goal of health and safety management.
</span></p><h2 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-hOGkXu NrNIR pf-130_ _Y6RW61"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-gyElHZ fxaypC pf-132_">Undesired circumstance
</span></h2><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Undesired_circumstance_-_Dr_Richard_Dune.png?v=1687527656" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Undesired_circumstance_-_Dr_Richard_Dune.png?v=1687527656 1536w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Undesired_circumstance_-_Dr_Richard_Dune_500x.png?v=1687527656 320w" width="1080" height="720" alt="Undesired circumstance - Dr Richard Dune -" title="Undesired circumstance - Dr Richard Dune -" data-pf-type="Image3" class="sc-bXTejn eKvewz pf-133_"/><p class="sc-FNXRL jGHEAN pf-134_" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-gyElHZ fxaypC pf-136_">An undesired circumstance involves a set of conditions that could lead to injury or ill health. Recognising and remedying these situations is fundamental to maintaining safety in care settings.
</span></p><h2 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-hOGkXu NrNIR pf-137_ _Y6RW61"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-gyElHZ fxaypC pf-139_">Health surveillance
</span></h2><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Health_surveillance_-_Dr_Richard_Dune.png?v=1687527775" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Health_surveillance_-_Dr_Richard_Dune.png?v=1687527775 1536w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Health_surveillance_-_Dr_Richard_Dune_500x.png?v=1687527775 320w" width="1310" height="767" alt="Health surveillance - Dr Richard Dune -" title="Health surveillance - Dr Richard Dune -" data-pf-type="Image3" class="sc-bXTejn eKvewz pf-140_"/><p class="sc-FNXRL jGHEAN pf-141_" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-gyElHZ fxaypC pf-143_">The process of monitoring the health of employees who are exposed to certain health risks due to the nature of their work.
</span></p><h2 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-hOGkXu NrNIR pf-144_ _Y6RW61"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-gyElHZ fxaypC pf-146_">Control measure
</span></h2><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Control_measure_-_Dr_Richard_Dune.png?v=1687527561" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Control_measure_-_Dr_Richard_Dune.png?v=1687527561 1536w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Control_measure_-_Dr_Richard_Dune_500x.png?v=1687527561 320w" width="1736" height="1157" alt="Control measure - Dr Richard Dune -" title="Control measure - Dr Richard Dune -" data-pf-type="Image3" class="sc-bXTejn eKvewz pf-147_"/><p class="sc-FNXRL jGHEAN pf-148_" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-gyElHZ fxaypC pf-150_">An action or activity designed to reduce the risk associated with a hazard. This can involve changes to work processes, using protective equipment, or implementing new safety protocols.
</span></p><h2 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-hOGkXu NrNIR pf-151_ _Y6RW61"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-gyElHZ fxaypC pf-153_">First aid
</span></h2><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/First_aid_-_Dr_Richard_Dune.png?v=1687527441" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/First_aid_-_Dr_Richard_Dune.png?v=1687527441 1536w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/First_aid_-_Dr_Richard_Dune_500x.png?v=1687527441 320w" width="1102" height="735" alt="First aid - Dr Richard Dune -" title="First aid - Dr Richard Dune -" data-pf-type="Image3" class="sc-bXTejn eKvewz pf-154_"/><p class="sc-FNXRL jGHEAN pf-155_" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-gyElHZ fxaypC pf-157_">Immediate care is provided to an injured or ill person until medical treatment is available. In a workplace setting, designated first aiders are typically trained to provide an initial response to health emergencies.
</span></p><h2 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-hOGkXu NrNIR pf-158_ _Y6RW61"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-gyElHZ fxaypC pf-160_">Personal protective equipment (PPE)
</span></h2><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Personal_protective_equipment_PPE_-_Dr_Richard_Dune.png?v=1687527045" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Personal_protective_equipment_PPE_-_Dr_Richard_Dune.png?v=1687527045 1536w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Personal_protective_equipment_PPE_-_Dr_Richard_Dune_500x.png?v=1687527045 320w" width="1800" height="1200" alt="Personal protective equipment (PPE) - Dr Richard Dune -" title="Personal protective equipment (PPE) - Dr Richard Dune -" data-pf-type="Image3" class="sc-bXTejn eKvewz pf-161_"/><p class="sc-FNXRL jGHEAN pf-162_" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-gyElHZ fxaypC pf-164_">Protective clothing or equipment designed to protect the wearer's body from injury or infection. PPE can include items like gloves, masks, and safety glasses.
</span></p><h2 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-hOGkXu NrNIR pf-165_ _Y6RW61"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-gyElHZ fxaypC pf-167_">Workplace exposure limit (WEL)
